25|$|As of March 2014, Air Traffic Control {{services}} for aircraft operating within the lateral and vertical {{limits of the}} Kalamazoo TRACON (Terminal Radar Approach Control) are being provided from a new ATC facility located at {{the east side of}} the airport. Edward Bowe, a Front <b>Line</b> <b>Manager</b> at the AZO ATC facility, retired April 1, 2014, after serving the community at Kalamazoo for 30 years and 10 months. A woman named Tanja Rowland took his position and became the youngest female in AZO history to become a front <b>line</b> <b>manager.</b>|$|E
